00:49:11,070 --> 00:49:14,972
Oh, no, Barbara.
You misunderstood.

709
00:49:15,040 --> 00:49:17,634
When I said
a home-cooked meal...

710
00:49:17,710 --> 00:49:22,170
I meant at my place...
I wanted to serve you.

711
00:49:22,248 --> 00:49:25,217
Oh, Zip.

712
00:49:25,284 --> 00:49:28,014
No man has ever
done this for me before.

713
00:49:28,087 --> 00:49:30,578
How thoughtful.

714
00:49:30,656 --> 00:49:33,489
- Well.
- And considerate.

715
00:49:33,559 --> 00:49:35,493
It's my pleasure.

716
00:49:35,561 --> 00:49:39,463
Oh, no, no, no. It's mine.

717
00:49:39,532 --> 00:49:43,161
- So, you'd like to come?
- Oh, yes.

718
00:49:43,235 --> 00:49:46,363
Yes. Yes.

719
00:49:46,438 --> 00:49:48,998
I can't wait.

720
00:49:49,074 --> 00:49:51,065
[Sighs]

721
00:49:53,479 --> 00:49:55,970
Seventy-third and Park.
And Barbara?

722
00:49:56,048 --> 00:50:00,712
- Yes, Zip?
- Thank you for being so flexible.

723
00:50:00,786 --> 00:50:03,550
No, Zip. Thank you.

724
00:50:21,640 --> 00:50:24,404
Oh, Zip!

725
00:50:24,476 --> 00:50:27,468
Everything looks divine.

726
00:50:29,181 --> 00:50:31,672
I have a funny feeling
that you've done...

727
00:50:31,750 --> 00:50:34,583
quite a bit of entertaining
for two here.

728
00:50:34,653 --> 00:50:37,622
Oh, I can honestly say
that until you...

729
00:50:37,690 --> 00:50:41,421
I haven't done any entertaining
for two here at all.

730
00:50:41,493 --> 00:50:43,984
You're certainly not
the average astronaut.

731
00:50:44,063 --> 00:50:48,124
Oh, I get so tired
of all that freeze-dried food.

732
00:50:48,200 --> 00:50:50,862
After a steady diet of pellet steak...

733
00:50:50,936 --> 00:50:52,870
and potato tablets...

734
00:50:52,938 --> 00:50:56,931
you yearn for something hot
to sink your teeth into.

735
00:51:01,146 --> 00:51:04,138
Well, you've whetted my appetite.

736
00:51:05,551 --> 00:51:08,213
It's not just your cooking.

737
00:51:10,222 --> 00:51:12,850
You are so well-rounded.

738
00:51:14,059 --> 00:51:18,291
Your collection of art
and antiques.

739
00:51:18,364 --> 00:51:20,832
You've made a real home here.

740
00:51:20,899 --> 00:51:24,494
Well, Earth still is
my favorite planet.

741
00:51:24,570 --> 00:51:27,437
No, I meant here, in New York.

742
00:51:27,506 --> 00:51:29,440
Oh.

743
00:51:29,508 --> 00:51:32,807
Most bachelors in this city are
only interested in an apartment...

744
00:51:32,878 --> 00:51:35,870
that comes fully loaded
with every gadget and contraption...

745
00:51:35,948 --> 00:51:39,616
man has invented
to snare a woman.

746
00:51:41,818 --> 00:51:46,084
I don't understand this, Peter.
How does a person lose their built-in bar?

747
00:51:46,155 --> 00:51:50,421
[Chuckles]
I swear, it was here a minute ago.

748
00:51:52,261 --> 00:51:55,389
- [Mechanical Whirring]
- Ohh!

749
00:51:55,465 --> 00:51:58,434
[Gasps]

750
00:52:02,538 --> 00:52:05,098
[Whirring]

751
00:52:05,174 --> 00:52:09,008
Hey. Found it. Vikki?

752
00:52:09,078 --> 00:52:12,275
Where are you?

753
00:52:12,348 --> 00:52:16,910
- [Vikki] I don't know.
- [Shrieks]

754
00:52:18,321 --> 00:52:20,881
Oh.

755
00:52:23,459 --> 00:52:27,759
Peter, your couch was all over me
like some animal.

756
00:52:27,830 --> 00:52:31,766
- Who knew you were so dangerous?
- I'm sorry.

757
00:52:31,834 --> 00:52:35,031
Uh, I know I seem
a little disoriented.

758
00:52:35,104 --> 00:52:38,130
Guess I tasted too much sherry
while I was cooking.

759
00:52:38,207 --> 00:52:42,268
You cooked for me?
No man has ever done that for me before.

760
00:52:42,345 --> 00:52:44,779
I'm famished.

761
00:52:44,847 --> 00:52:48,248
Actually, I didn't cook... here...

762
00:52:48,317 --> 00:52:50,911
at my apartment... for us.

763
00:52:50,987 --> 00:52:55,981
I cooked... at Catch's apartment
for... Catch.

764
00:52:56,059 --> 00:53:00,086
- Oh.
- But you've only been here a minute.

765
00:53:00,163 --> 00:53:03,860
Let's make it 10 and see
if we forget all about dinner.

766
00:53:09,172 --> 00:53:12,141
- [Vikki] Are those your parents?
- No. Those are Catch's parents.

767
00:53:12,208 --> 00:53:15,473
Why do you have a picture
of Catch's parents?

768
00:53:16,512 --> 00:53:19,743
Let's listen to some music.

769
00:53:27,990 --> 00:53:30,823
[Whirring]

770
00:53:33,696 --> 00:53:38,429
[Stereo: "1812 Overture'"
At Full Volume]

771
00:53:39,435 --> 00:53:41,767
[Continues]

772
00:53:41,838 --> 00:53:44,500
It's all right. It's all right.

773
00:53:44,574 --> 00:53:47,338
[Both]
Ooh!

774
00:53:47,410 --> 00:53:49,605
- [Slingshot Sound]
- Ooh!

775
00:53:51,280 --> 00:53:53,714
[Both Gasp]

776
00:53:53,783 --> 00:53:56,616
Ooh!

777
00:53:56,686 --> 00:54:00,713
I can't do this for eight more minutes.
Let's go eat.

778
00:54:00,790 --> 00:54:03,691
- [Vikki Screeches]
- ["1812 Overture'"Ends]

779
00:54:07,830 --> 00:54:11,027
- [Catcher] How's that?
- [Barbara] Oh.

780
00:54:11,100 --> 00:54:14,160
[Catcher]
You tell me when it's good for you.

781
00:54:14,237 --> 00:54:18,799
Put your hand on it and guide me
till I got it in the right spot.

782
00:54:18,875 --> 00:54:22,675
[Barbara]
Almost. Almost.

783
00:54:22,745 --> 00:54:24,838
Oh, Zip.

784
00:54:24,914 --> 00:54:30,443
I've done this a lot before, of course,
but never with such a powerful instrument.

785
00:54:30,520 --> 00:54:35,321
[Barbara Gasps]
That's it.

786
00:54:35,391 --> 00:54:39,418
It's perfectly clear.

787
00:54:42,532 --> 00:54:46,662
Oh, Zip, I've never seen anything
so beautiful...

788
00:54:46,736 --> 00:54:48,897
in all my life.

789
00:54:48,971 --> 00:54:53,408
- Neither have I.
- You're not even looking
through the telescope.

790
00:54:53,476 --> 00:54:55,944
I know.

791
00:55:14,764 --> 00:55:18,029
This chocolate souffle
is delicious, Zip.

792
00:55:18,100 --> 00:55:20,796
You've really outdone yourself.

793
00:55:20,870 --> 00:55:24,067
- I wanted the perfect end
to the perfect evening.
- Mm.

794
00:55:24,140 --> 00:55:27,507
I've never been more ready
to go to bed.

795
00:55:27,577 --> 00:55:32,173
Oh, Zip, I'm so glad
that you feel that way.

796
00:55:32,248 --> 00:55:36,548
- You know that I feel the same way?
- Well, then, let's get to bed.

797
00:55:36,619 --> 00:55:40,453
- [Inhales Deeply]
- I'll call you a taxi.

798
00:55:42,325 --> 00:55:46,193
- Taxi?
- [Dial Tone]

799
00:55:46,262 --> 00:55:52,132
Oh, when I said bed,
you thought I meant bed.

800
00:55:52,201 --> 00:55:55,136
Oh, Barbara, I'm so sorry.

801
00:55:55,204 --> 00:55:58,173
This is only the first time you've ever
been to my home, and where I come from...

802
00:55:58,241 --> 00:56:02,075
It's all right, Zip.

803
00:56:02,144 --> 00:56:06,581
It's all right.
Um, it's better this way.

804
00:56:08,217 --> 00:56:12,586
Let's, um...
Let's just say good night...

805
00:56:14,490 --> 00:56:16,856
and good-bye.

806
00:56:16,926 --> 00:56:20,293
- Good-bye? You mean for good?
- I'm afraid so, Zip.

807
00:56:20,363 --> 00:56:23,264
You see,
I'm beginning to feel...

808
00:56:23,332 --> 00:56:26,267
Well, I'm beginning to feel.

809
00:56:26,335 --> 00:56:30,169
Well, couldn't you give me
just one more chance?

810
00:56:30,239 --> 00:56:34,232
Oh, I'd like to, Zip,
really, I would...

811
00:56:34,310 --> 00:56:37,279
but just the fact that I'd like to
give you another chance...

812
00:56:37,346 --> 00:56:41,510
is the very reason
why I absolutely must not.

813
00:57:14,183 --> 00:57:17,209
Okay. One more chance.

814
00:57:20,222 --> 00:57:24,625
[Clears Throat]
I'll just, um...

815
00:57:24,694 --> 00:57:27,390
Hmm.

816
00:58:00,863 --> 00:58:04,128
[Laughter, Chattering]

817
00:58:11,707 --> 00:58:14,642
[Chattering Continues]

818
00:58:35,297 --> 00:58:38,425
- Peter?
- You rang?

819
00:58:38,501 --> 00:58:41,470
No. I used my key, Maynard.
How did everyone else get in here?

820
00:58:41,537 --> 00:58:44,973
I took Vikki down to the Village
for a demitasse. Crazy!

821
00:58:45,041 --> 00:58:48,738
And then the coffeehouse got raided,
so I moved the scene uptown.

822
00:58:48,811 --> 00:58:52,645
- You dig, Daddy-O?
- Oh, I do dig.

823
00:58:52,715 --> 00:58:58,017
And after being grounded for 24 days,
this astronaut is ready to blast off.

824
00:59:03,459 --> 00:59:07,088
- Ask me why I mourn.
- Why do you mourn, baby?

825
00:59:07,163 --> 00:59:10,223
I mourn because you are shrouded
in the suit and tie...

826
00:59:10,299 --> 00:59:12,995
that Madison Avenue
will bury you in alive.

827
00:59:13,069 --> 00:59:17,028
Well, if it'll cheer you up,
you can help me out of it.

828
00:59:30,886 --> 00:59:32,085
- Hi!
- Hi! Coffee?

829
00:59:32,085 --> 00:59:34,781
- Hi!
- Hi! Coffee?

830
00:59:34,854 --> 00:59:38,221
So, this is a beatnik party.

831
00:59:38,291 --> 00:59:40,691
- Isn't it a gas?
- Yes!

832
00:59:40,760 --> 00:59:44,696
Oh, I'm so glad you called.
After the date I had tonight, I
really didn't want to be alone.

833
00:59:44,764 --> 00:59:47,995
Well, you won't need an astronaut to
find a date here. Everyone's in orbit.

834
00:59:48,067 --> 00:59:52,401
So, should I introduce myself to
the host, or is that too Establishment?

835
00:59:52,472 --> 00:59:55,202
You know the host.
This is Peter's place.

836
00:59:55,274 --> 00:59:58,368
- Catcher Block's
not going to be here, is he?
- Oh, not to worry.

837
00:59:58,444 --> 01:00:00,969
Everyone here is a total stranger.

838
01:00:01,047 --> 01:00:04,073
Go throw your coat on the bed,
and let's join the bash!

839
01:00:12,225 --> 01:00:14,693
Oh, excuse me.

840
01:00:14,760 --> 01:00:17,320
- Catch.
- Yes?

841
01:00:19,065 --> 01:00:21,090
Zip?

842
01:00:21,167 --> 01:00:25,331
[Catcher]
Barbara. Barbara, wait.

843
01:00:25,404 --> 01:00:28,430
- Barbara!
- [Elevator Bell Dings]

844
01:00:28,508 --> 01:00:32,911
- Barbara, wait! I can explain.
- You don't have to explain.

845
01:00:32,979 --> 01:00:37,279
You said you were ready for bed.
I'm glad you ran into someone
to take to bed with you.

846
01:00:37,350 --> 01:00:41,116
- But it wasn't like that.
I don't even know her.
- Oh, really!

847
01:00:41,187 --> 01:00:43,519
I mean, I didn't know
what I was doin'.

848
01:00:43,589 --> 01:00:47,047
And yet her hat's off
to you anyway!

849
01:00:47,126 --> 01:00:49,390
What?

850
01:00:59,539 --> 01:01:02,804
- Good night, miss.
- [Bell Dings]

851
01:01:04,177 --> 01:01:06,611
Good night, Major Martin.

852
01:01:06,679 --> 01:01:09,648
Barbara, you gotta believe me.
I did not know what was happening.

853
01:01:09,715 --> 01:01:13,811
The minute I got here, that girl
filled my pipe with some tobacco
she bought in San Francisco.

854
01:01:13,886 --> 01:01:16,753
After that,
everything went hoo-whee!

855
01:01:16,822 --> 01:01:20,781
- You mean she drugged you?
- All the way into that bedroom.

856
01:01:20,860 --> 01:01:24,455
Wait a minute. What were you doing
at a party like that?

857
01:01:24,530 --> 01:01:27,829
I had no idea there was
gonna be a party here.

858
01:01:27,900 --> 01:01:32,132
I got a call after you left to tell me
to come to this publisher's apartment...

859
01:01:32,205 --> 01:01:36,505
to meet some journalist
who wanted to do a cover story
on my NASA top-secret project.

860
01:01:36,576 --> 01:01:41,172
- Some guy named Snitch or Snatch.
- Catch? Catcher Block?

861
01:01:41,247 --> 01:01:45,581
Maybe. Anyway, I rush over here,
and that guy does not even show up.

862
01:01:45,651 --> 01:01:49,417
- Don't you see? You were set up.
- No!

863
01:01:49,488 --> 01:01:52,787
Yes! Catcher Block
invited you here...

864
01:01:52,858 --> 01:01:56,794
under false pretenses so he could
do one of his famous exposes...

865
01:01:56,862 --> 01:02:00,559
on how NASA's
top-secret New York project...

866
01:02:00,633 --> 01:02:03,898
is just one big,
drug-infested beatnik shindig.

867
01:02:03,970 --> 01:02:06,939
- Oh, that's low!
- That's Catcher Block!

868
01:02:07,006 --> 01:02:11,466
- That's how he operates.!
- Oh, Barbara, I'm so sorry.

869
01:02:11,544 --> 01:02:16,072
I just feel like such
"a" easily tricked hick...

870
01:02:16,148 --> 01:02:20,847
and then you went
and made the trick seem so obvious.

871
01:02:20,920 --> 01:02:25,983
Oh, Zip, I didn't mean
to make you feel bad.

872
01:02:26,058 --> 01:02:29,619
I didn't mean
to make you feel mad.

873
01:02:29,695 --> 01:02:32,789
Oh, this is terrible.

874
01:02:32,865 --> 01:02:36,733
We're behaving just like
two people in love.

875
01:02:38,537 --> 01:02:41,199
Which means this argument was
the final straw. This has to be the end.

876
01:02:41,274 --> 01:02:43,834
Or just the beginning.
Holy cow.

877
01:02:43,909 --> 01:02:48,846
This argument has made me realize
that I must really care about you.

878
01:02:48,914 --> 01:02:52,145
I'm finally ready
to get to know you better.

879
01:02:52,218 --> 01:02:54,413
How much better?

880
01:02:54,487 --> 01:02:56,887
All the way better.

881
01:02:56,956 --> 01:03:00,915
- Really?
- I'm sorry I have to say this, Barbara...

882
01:03:00,993 --> 01:03:05,555
but... I love you.

883
01:03:05,631 --> 01:03:09,727
Well, I don't have any rules...

884
01:03:09,802 --> 01:03:11,861
against men falling in love.

885
01:03:11,937 --> 01:03:15,429
So I can make love to you...

886
01:03:15,508 --> 01:03:20,377
heartfelt, passionate,
worshipping, adoring love...

887
01:03:20,446 --> 01:03:23,176
and you could still have
meaningless sex with me, right?

888
01:03:23,249 --> 01:03:25,683
Yes.

889
01:03:25,751 --> 01:03:28,914
So are we still on
for tomorrow night?

890
01:03:28,988 --> 01:03:31,218
Yes.

891
01:03:31,290 --> 01:03:34,225
Oh, yes.
[Sighs]

892
01:03:36,696 --> 01:03:39,927
That pink book is ruining my life.!

893
01:03:39,999 --> 01:03:42,866
Woman acts as if
she has a mind of her own.

894
01:03:42,935 --> 01:03:45,062
She refuses my advances.

895
01:03:45,137 --> 01:03:48,106
This goes straight to the sanctity
of a man's most fundamental right.

896
01:03:48,174 --> 01:03:50,199
All our wives
are giving us trouble.

897
01:03:50,276 --> 01:03:53,245
I'm not talking about my wife.
I'm talking about my mistress.

898
01:03:54,380 --> 01:03:57,372
I want that Vikki Hiller fired!

899
01:03:57,450 --> 01:04:01,409
But you can't fire her now, T.B.

900
01:04:01,487 --> 01:04:04,650
How would it look?

901
01:04:04,724 --> 01:04:07,591
She is the most celebrated editor
in the business.

902
01:04:07,660 --> 01:04:09,594
You're my creative team.

903
01:04:09,662 --> 01:04:12,153
Create a reason to get rid of her...

904
01:04:12,231 --> 01:04:15,064
or I'll create a new creative team.

905
01:04:17,536 --> 01:04:21,529
- [Door Slams]
- [Elevator Bell Dings]

906
01:04:21,607 --> 01:04:26,067
- [Receptionist Talking, Indistinct]
- Good morning, gentlemen.

907
01:04:26,145 --> 01:04:28,079
Do you know why it's good?

908
01:04:28,147 --> 01:04:31,639
Because this is the morning
I tell Theodore Banner that
my fellow senior editors...

909
01:04:31,717 --> 01:04:35,175
are going to treat me like more
than just a titular senior editor...

910
01:04:35,254 --> 01:04:38,690
or I quit.
[Sighs]

911
01:04:45,998 --> 01:04:49,559
I should've known
the top dog would be a rat.

912
01:04:49,635 --> 01:04:52,195
He's a man. I hate men.

913
01:04:52,271 --> 01:04:56,105
For as man-crazy as I've been
my whole life, I sure can't stand 'em.

914
01:04:56,175 --> 01:05:00,544
- I think I'll just get married.
- You're upset. You'll find another job.

915
01:05:00,613 --> 01:05:02,308
I don't want another job.

916
01:05:02,381 --> 01:05:06,340
I'm sorry, but I don't wanna be
a Down With Love girl anymore.

917
01:05:06,419 --> 01:05:12,153
I give up. I give in. I just wanna
be Mrs. Peter MacMannus.

918
01:05:12,224 --> 01:05:13,714
Really?

919
01:05:13,793 --> 01:05:17,160
At least then there'd be one man
I could tell what to do.

920
01:05:17,229 --> 01:05:20,528
Anyway. There. I've said it.

921
01:05:20,599 --> 01:05:24,933
- If you also want me to resign
as your friend, I understand.
- Oh, Vikki, no!

922
01:05:25,004 --> 01:05:27,495
How could I possibly accept
your resignation now...

923
01:05:27,573 --> 01:05:29,973
when I need a friend
more than ever?

924
01:05:30,042 --> 01:05:34,502
You see, I have a confession
to make too.

925
01:05:34,580 --> 01:05:38,414
I'm not a Down With Love girl either.
I'm a woman who's fallen in love.

926
01:05:38,484 --> 01:05:42,045
And I'm gonna tell him.
And tonight's the night.

927
01:05:42,121 --> 01:05:45,056
- Tonight?
- Yep.

928
01:05:45,124 --> 01:05:48,855
Tonight's the night
Barbara Novak is going down.

929
01:05:48,928 --> 01:05:51,158
I've got her exactly
where I want her.

930
01:05:51,230 --> 01:05:53,926
She was saying yes, but any man
could tell she really meant no.

931
01:05:53,999 --> 01:05:57,696
- Uh-oh.
- Here's the title
to next month's cover story...

932
01:05:57,770 --> 01:06:02,207
"Catcher Block on Barbara Novak:
Penetrating the Myth."

933
01:06:02,274 --> 01:06:05,175
We'll have to sell it
in a brown wrapper.

934
01:06:05,244 --> 01:06:07,212
I'm taking her to my place,
which she still thinks is your place...

935
01:06:07,279 --> 01:06:10,544
by saying the guy she thinks I am, who acts
like you, has a meeting there with you...

936
01:06:10,616 --> 01:06:12,777
and the guy who she still
doesn't know I really am.

937
01:06:12,852 --> 01:06:16,686
- What do I have to say?
- You don't say a word.

938
01:06:16,755 --> 01:06:20,054
Gotcha. So this is it?
Tonight's the night?

939
